          <p>Jack the Ripper is infamously known for terrorizing Whitchapel, a district in London in 1888. The unknown serial killer gained popularity for his bloody murders.</p>
  
          <p>There were only five confirmed and eleven unconfirmed murders committed by Jack. Because of these murders, Jack became one of the most popular serial killers of all time.</p>
  
          <p>The identity of the murderer has not yet been revealed. But many accusations pinned the murders on a 23 year old polish barber, Aaron Kosminski. Sadly, since there was not enough evidence against Aaron Kosminski, he was not sentenced to any jail time.</p>
  
